dc_title_s: Plan of the city of Washington in the territory of Columbia : ceded by the states of Virginia and Maryland to the United States of America, and by them established as the seat of their government, after the year MDCCC
dc_description_s: Shows block numbers and proposed government buildings.  Relief shown by hachures. Depths shown by soundings.  Also covers Georgetown.  Watermark: [crown over fleur-de-lis].  Includes text, notes, and coat-of-arms.|70 x 80 centimeters|Scale approximately 1:19,800|City Maps
